column5: Anybody ever fish this Lake in Saskatchewan? Would love to hear about it.
I seem to remember the name, means walleye, I think, is it on the Hanson Road, or up toward Pelican Narrows? I do know I didn't fish it, tho. Bill
Your right Bill.French for walleye.Wonder what the French word is for pickerel which is actually the proper name.
I always hear the French say Bonjour,that must mean pickerel.
My guess at bonjour would be "good trip", but my Czech heritage never taught me any French, although I had a couple years of HS Latin, like a hundred years ago. Bill
You only need to learn one word now,,,very easy,,,,,,EH!!!!!!
